parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or slip out of gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates to engage
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting
the transmission makes loud noises or grinding sounds
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key can be removed from the ignition while the vehicle is not in park
the vehicle stalls or does not start
the ignition switch or interlock system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to slip or hesitate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates to engage
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting
the transmission makes loud noises or grinding sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle will not start
the ignition switch is faulty
the ignition switch has abnormal wear on switch contacts
the plastic body of the switch is melted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower ball joint can cause the front suspension to collapse, leading to a loss of vehicle control, deceleration, and reduced steering controllability, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Clunking or squeaking sounds from the front or rear of the vehicle
especially when driving over bumps
uneven roads
or in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The noise from the rear suspension can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, potentially leading to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud squeaking or clunking sounds from the rear of the vehicle
especially when driving over bumps or in cold weather.
